

Kevin Peter Pietersen MBE (born 27 June 1980 in Pietermaritzburg, KwaZulu-Natal Province|Natal, South Africa) is an English cricketer. He is an attacking right-handed batsman and occasional off spin bowler who plays for Hampshire County Cricket Club and is a member of both the England Test match and One Day International teams. 

He made his First-class cricket|first-class debut for Natal in 1997 before moving to England after voicing his displeasure at the racial quota system in place in South Africa,;[http://content-usa.cricinfo.com/england/content/player/19296.html Kevin Pietersen biography], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; and in order to further his opportunities for playing at international level.Being born of an English mother gave Pietersen eligibility to play for England, and after serving a qualifying period of four years playing at county level, he was called up almost immediately into the national side. He made his international debut in the One-day International match against Zimbabwe in 2004,;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/8/8063/One-Day_International_Matches.html One-day International Matches played by Kevin Pietersen], Cricketarchive. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; and his Test match debut in the 2005 Ashes series against Australia the following year.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/8/8063/Test_Matches.html Test Matches played by Kevin Pietersen], Cricketarchive. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; 

Pietersen quickly became the fastest batsman to reach both 1000 and 2000 runs in One-day International cricket,;[http://www.cricinfo.com/db/STATS/ODIS/BATTING/FASTEST_ODI_CAREER_RUNS/ODI_FASTEST_TO_1000_RUNS.html ODIs - Fastest to 1000 Career Runs], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;;Rajesh, S and Gopalakrishna, HR. &quot;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/wc2007/content/story/291874.html Pietersen breaks a jinx]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2007-04-21. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; and currently has the highest average of any England player to have played more than 20 innings of one-day cricket.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/England/Odis/Career_Batting_by_Average.html Career Batting and Fielding for England in ODIs] Cricketarchive. Retrieved on 2007-06-03.; He also has the second-highest run total from his first 25 Tests, behind only the Australian Donald Bradman.;Brenkley, Stephen. &quot;[http://sport.independent.co.uk/cricket/article2586624.ece Second Test: Pietersen plunders before the collapse]&quot;, The Independent, 2007-05-27. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; He became only the third English batsman to top the ICC One-day International rankings, doing so in March 2007.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvaus/content/story/287248.html Pietersen jumps to top of ODI rankings]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2007-03-26. Retrieved 2007-06-06.;

Early and personal life
Born of an English mother and an Afrikaner father, Penny and Jannie,; Pietersen had a strict and well-disciplined childhood, along with his three brothers Tony, Greg and Bryan;;[http://kevin-pietersen.tripod.com/id1.html The Man with the Hair]. Retrieved on 2007-06-05.; he learned valuable lessons from this &quot;fantastic&quot; approach to parenting, and said: &quot;Discipline is good. It taught me that I didn't always have to have what I wanted; that what I needed was different from what I wanted.&quot;;Cooke, Rachel. &quot;[http://observer.guardian.co.uk/osm/story/0,,1882063,00.html 'I was up at six. I've a party to go to. So what is it you want?']&quot;, The Observer, 2006-10-01. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; Bryan is currently playing club and second XI cricket in England.;&quot;[http://www.wansteadandwoodfordguardian.co.uk/sport/cricket/display.var.849912.0.pietersen_looks_for_essex_move.php Pietersen looks for Essex move]&quot;, Guardian-Series, 2006-07-27. Retrieved on 2007-05-31.;

Pietersen attended Maritzburg College, Pietermaritzburg, and made his first-class cricket debut for Natal's B team in 1997, aged 17, where he was regarded predominantly as an off spin bowler and a hard-hitting lower-order batsman.;Brenkley, Stephen. &quot;[http://sport.independent.co.uk/cricket/article10464.ece Pietersen faces sternest test on home turf].&quot; The Independent, 2005-02-11. Retrieved on 2007-05-29.;;Borland, Ken. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/ci/content/story/92818.html Nottinghamshire sign young South African]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2000-10-03. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; After two seasons, he moved to England for a five-month spell as the overseas player for club side Cannock CC, and helped them win the Birmingham and District Premier League in 2000.;&quot;[http://www.expressandstar.co.uk/2006/09/06/pietersen-in-cricket-club-row/ Pietersen in cricket club row]&quot;, Express &amp; Star, 2006-09-06. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; This first spell away from home did not leave him with fond memories for England, in particular &quot;those horrible Black Country accents&quot;, living in a single room above a squash court, and working in the club bar.;However, he returned to newly-renamed KwaZulu Natal side a better cricketer, a lack of opportunities to bowl having improved his batting.; 

Pietersen is widely portrayed in the media as having a self-assured personality, described by Geoffrey Boycott as being &quot;cocky and confident&quot;.;Boycott, Geoffrey. &quot;[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/main.jhtml?xml=/sport/2005/09/13/scboyc13.xml Warne lets the urn slip from his grasp]&quot;, The Telegraph, 2005-12-09. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; England test captain Michael Vaughan counters this, saying, &quot;KP is not a confident person. He obviously has great belief in his ability but that's not quite the same thing...And I know KP wants to be loved. I try to text him and talk to him as often as I can because I know he is insecure.&quot;;McRae, Donald. &quot;[http://sport.guardian.co.uk/cricket/story/0,10069,1594567,00.html Psychology that guides England's man of steel]&quot;, The Guardian, 2005-10-18. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; He has been noted for his unusual haircuts, with his peroxide blond dyed streak of hair along the middle of his head during the 2005 Ashes series being described as a &quot;dead skunk&quot; look.;William, Richard. &quot;[http://www.guardian.co.uk/uk_news/story/0,,1568634,00.html After 16 years, to England, the Ashes]&quot;, The Guardian, 2005-09-13. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; During the 2006-07 Ashes|2006&amp;ndash;07 Ashes tour, the Australian team, noted for their efforts to dominate opponents psychologically, dubbed him &quot;The Ego&quot;, or &quot;FIGJAM&quot; (Fuck I'm Good, Just Ask Me).;Fraser, Angus. &quot;[http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4158/is_20061230/ai_n17091835- Buchanan slates Pietersen for selfish attitude]&quot;, The Independent, 2006-12-30. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;Other nicknames include ''KP'', ''Kelves'' and ''Kapes''.;

Pietersen was rumoured to be dating model Caprice Bourret who accompanied him to the ICC awards in October 2005,;&quot;[http://www.ecb.co.uk/england/pietersen-scoops-icc-award,6395,EN.html Ashes stars collect ICC Prizes]&quot;, ecb.co.uk. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; but he is now married to Liberty X singer Jessica Taylor.;Greenstreet, Rosanna. &quot;[http://www.guardian.co.uk/weekend/story/0,,1861841,00.html Q&amp;A]&quot;, The Guardian, 2006-09-02. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; The couple married on 29 December 2007 at the Manor House Hotel in Wiltshire, with former England team-mate Darren Gough acting as best man.;Baker, Andrew. &quot;[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/main.jhtml?xml=/sport/2007/04/18/scbake18.xml Dancing to Gough's tune]&quot;, The Telegraph, 2007-04-18. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;

Domestic career
He impressed members of Nasser Hussain's England side when playing for KwaZulu Natal in 1999; he took four top-order wickets and, despite batting at number nine, scored 61 not out from 57 balls, hitting four sixes.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/1999-2000/ENG_IN_RSA/SCORECARDS/ENG_KZN_03-06DEC1999.html KwaZulu-Natal v England XI 3-6 December 1999], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; Hussain then recommended that Pietersen secure a contract with an English county side.;Compton, Patrick. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/ci/content/story/78799.html Hussain impressed with Pieterson]&quot;, Cricinfo, 1999-12-06. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;

Despite the praise from the England side, Pietersen was dropped from the Natal first team. Pietersen felt that this was due to the country's racial quota system, in which provincial sides were required to have at least four non-white players.;;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/ci/content/story/270556.html Pietersen in the eye of a storm]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-12-01. Retrieved on 2007-06-04.;;McRae, Donald. &quot;[http://sport.guardian.co.uk/ashes2005/story/0,15993,1519454,00.html The heartache that honed a hardcore hitter]&quot;, The Guardian, 2005-07-02. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; Pietersen's view was that players should be judged on merit, and described it as &quot;heartbreaking&quot; when he was left out of the side, although he later reflected &quot;it turned out it was the best thing that could have happened&quot;.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/258181.html Racial quotas led Pietersen to leave South Africa]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-08-30. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; Pietersen has since firmly criticised the quota system,;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/6198644.stm SA hit back at Pietersen comments]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2006-12-01. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; which he feels forced him out of the country of his birth. He has also criticised Graeme Smith, who became captain of the South African side in 2003, calling him &quot;an absolute muppet, childish and strange&quot; and that his behaviour &quot;leaves a lot to be desired&quot;.;&quot;[http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/sport/article-23376544-details/Pietersen%20could%20face%20four-Test%20ban/article.do Pietersen could face four-test ban]&quot;, thisislondon.co.uk, 2006-11-30. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; Smith opposed this, saying, &quot;I'm patriotic about my country, and that's why I don't like Kevin Pietersen. The only reason that Kevin and I have never had a relationship is because he slated South Africa&quot;.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/ci/content/story/258408.html Graeme Smith slams Pietersen]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-09-02. Retrieved on 2007-06-05.; His outspoken views published in his autobiography, ''Crossing the Boundary'', in September 2006, and in an interview for South African magazine ''GQ'', led to unsuccessful calls for an ICC investigation regarding bringing the game into disrepute.;Pietersen, Kevin (2006). ''Crossing the Boundary: The Early Years in my Cricketing Life''. Ebury Press. ISBN 0091912059.;;

In 2000, Nottinghamshire coach Clive Rice, who had seen Pietersen play in 1997 in South Africa at a schools week, heard that Pietersen was playing club cricket in Birmingham and offered him a three-year contract to play for the county.;His maiden first-class century came on his Nottinghamshire debut against Loughborough UCCE.;Collins, Sam. &quot;[http://www.cricinfo.com/kevinpietersenzone/timeline.html Rise of a star]&quot;, Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2005-05-28.; In his first season he made 1,275 runs with an impressive batting average of 57.95,;Booth, Lawrence. &quot;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/wisdencricketer/content/story/134539.html Southern comfort]&quot;, The Wisden Cricketer, April 2004. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; including 218 not out in an unbroken sixth-wicket stand of 352 with John Morris at Derby in July, after having been out lbw for a duck in the first innings.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/counties/1465474.stm Pietersen enjoys run feast]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2001-07-30. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; These performances led to praise in the ''Wisden Cricketers' Almanack'': &quot;If he can maintain his first season's form, the name of Pietersen should be pencilled in for future Test squads.&quot;; This form did indeed continue into the following year: he made another unbeaten double-century, against Middlesex, taking part in a partnership of 316 for the fourth wicket with Darren Bicknell.;[http://sl.cricinfo.com/link_to_database/ARCHIVE/2002/ENG_LOCAL/CC2/SCORECARDS/14-19AUG2002/NOTTS_MIDDX_CC2_14-17AUG2002.htmlNottinghamshire v Middlesex, 14-16 August 2002], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; This period proved to be a purple patch for the batsman, scoring four consecutive centuries (254 not out, 122, 147 and 116) in one week in August.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/counties/2210644.stm Pietersen piles on the runs]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2002-08-22. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; 

In 2003, Pietersen scored 1,546 first-class cricket|first-class runs, and 764 runs in limited overs cricket.;;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/8/8063/a_Batting_by_Season.html List A Batting and Fielding in Each Season by Kevin Pietersen], Cricketarchive. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; He was selected for the 2003&amp;ndash;04 ECB National Academy tour of India, and had a successful tour scoring 523 runs including three centuries in his six first-class innings to record an average of 104.60,;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/8/8063/f_Batting_by_Season.html First-class Batting and Fielding in Each Season by Kevin Pietersen], Cricketarchive. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;and making 131 in a one-day match against India A in Bangalore.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/79/79041.html India A v England A in 2003/4], Cricketarchive, 2004-02-10. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;

After Nottinghamshire were relegated in 2003, Pietersen requested a release from his contract, saying &quot;I haven't been happy for a while....The pitch at Trent Bridge has been one of my problems... I could have done so much better if the wicket had been good.&quot;;&quot;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/wisdencricketer/content/story/132889.html Pietersen confirms he wants to quit Notts]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2003-10-15. Retrieved on 2007-06-05.; This led to a public row with club captain Jason Gallian, where Gallian allegedly threw Pietersen's kit off the Trent Bridge balcony and broke his bat:
;During the game I told the captain that I was not happy and that I wanted to leave. After the game we spoke in the dressing room and then I went to have dinner. I got a call saying the captain had trashed my equipment. I was told the captain had said, 'if he does not want to play for Notts he can f*** off.' I have not spoken to Gallian since, nor have I received an apology.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/136698.html Pietersen seeks release from Nottinghamshire]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2004-01-16. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;; Pietersen was made to honour the last year of his contract at Nottinghamshire, but &quot;didn't enjoy it at all&quot;.;John, Emma. &quot;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/wisdencricketer/content/story/146400.html The only lane is the fast lane]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-03-23. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; In October 2004, he joined Hampshire under the captaincy of Shane Warne.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/142765.html Pietersen signs for Hampshire], Cricinfo, 2004-10-26. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;

After becoming a regular in the international side, Pietersen rarely gets an opportunity to play domestic cricket. Having an England &quot;central contract&quot; means that Pietersen is only released to play for Hampshire at the discretion of the national coach. After being left out of the national side to face Bangladesh in May 2005, Pietersen had several good innings in the four-day county championship, including two centuries.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/ci/content/story/209752.html Pietersen posts another reminder]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-05-21. Retrieved on 2007-06-03.; He only played twice for the county in 2006, and has played once so far in 2007, with an unbeaten 66 against Ireland.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/107/107510.html Hampshire v Ireland], Cricketarchive, 2007-05-07. Retrieved on 2007-06-03.;

International career
Success in South Africa

The tour of Zimbabwe caused several players to voice their concerns about the Robert Mugabe regime, the security issues inthe country and the standard of the Zimbabwean side.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/zimbabwe/content/story/143154.html England agree to five-match series in Zimbabwe]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2004-09-09. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; Steve Harmison was the first to boycott the tour for &quot;political and sporting reasons&quot;,;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvwi/content/story/143416.html Harmison opts out of Zimbabwe tour]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2004-09-19. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; and all-rounder Andrew Flintoff was reported to be considering taking a moral stand himself. The England Chairman of Selectors David Graveney denied that the selectors would leave out players unhappy with touring Zimbabwe and would put their absences down to injury.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvwi/content/story/143599.html Full-strength side will tour Zimbabwe]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2004-09-26. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; Flintoff was, however, &quot;rested&quot; and Pietersen rushed into the squad &quot;at the earliest opportunity&quot;.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvwi/content/story/143632.html Flintoff and Trescothick stay at home]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2004-09-28. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; In the five match ODI series, Pietersen batted in three innings which included a score of 77 not out; he finished the series with an average of 104.00 as England won the series 4&amp;ndash;0.

Pietersen was upset not to be initially in the squad to tour South Africa.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/142649.html Pietersen hits out at non-selection]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2004-10-20. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; With Flintoff withdrawing due to injury,;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvwi/content/story/145551.html Flintoff surgery is confirmed]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-01-25. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; Pietersen was recalled to the squad,;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/ci/content/story/145268.html Pietersen added to England's one-day squad]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-01-14. Retrieved on 2007-05-29.; and cemented his place in the first team with 97 off 84 balls in the warm-up match against South Africa A, in the face of a hostile crowd.;Majendie, Matt. &quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/4215057.stm Pietersen enters South Africa cauldron]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2005-01-28. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; Throughout the tour, Pietersen was subjected to a barrage of abuse from the South African crowd, who regarded him somewhat like a traitor.; He said:
;I knew I was going to cop a lot of stick but it will be like water off a duck's back...I expected stick at the start of the innings, and I'm sure it will carry on through the whole series. But I just sat back and laughed at the opposition, with their swearing and 'traitor' remarks... some of them can hardly speak English. My affiliation is with England. In fact, I'm starting to speak too much like Darren Gough... In fact, I'm going to get one of Gough's tattoos with three lions and my number underneath...No one can say I'm not English.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/ci/content/story/145622.html Pietersen says abuse is 'water off a duck's back']&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-01-28. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; 
;

Pietersen scored a 96-ball 108 not out in the The result in cricket#tie|tied second ODI at Bloemfontein, after which the crowd turned their backs on him as he returned to the pavilion.;Miller, Andrew. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/144265.html It's a tie after a last-ball thriller]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-02-02. Retrieved on 2007-05-27; This score set his ODI average at an incredible record 234.00.;[http://www.sportstats.com.au/blognov04tojun05.html Z-score’s Cricket Stats Blog Archive, Nov 2004 to Jun 2005]. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;;[http://www.howstat.com/cricket/Statistics/Players/PlayerProgressSummary_ODI.asp?PlayerID=3238 HowStat! ODI Kevin Pietersen:Batting - Progressive Average and Aggregate], HowStat. Retrieved 2007-05-28.; He made 75 at Cape Town,;Thompson, Jenny. &quot;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/ci/content/story/144350.html South Africa trounce England by 108 runs]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-02-06. Retrieved on 2007-05-27; then at East London Pietersen made an unbeaten 100 from only 69 balls, the fastest century by an England player in a one-day match,;Thompson, Jenny. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/144479.html Pietersen century all in vain]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-02-09. Retrieved on 2007-05-26.; although England still lost by eight runs. In the final game at Centurion Park, Pietersen came to the wicket at 32/3 and scored 116, but again could not prevent a defeat. Pietersen ended the series, which England lost 4&amp;ndash;1, with 454 runs in five innings, and the Player of the Series award.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/4260173.stm England sign off with fourth loss]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2005-02-13. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Seasons/RSA/2004-05_RSA_England_in_South_Africa_2004-05.html England in South Africa 2004/05], Cricketarchive. Retrieved on 28 May, 2007.; By the end of the series, the South African crowds had generally replaced hostility with respect for Pietersen, his final century being awarded a standing ovation.;Fraser, Angus. &quot;[http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4158/is_20050802/ai_n14827270 Cricket: Giles' amazing show of insecurity invites the Australians]&quot;, The Independent, 2005-08-02. Retrieved on 2007-02-27.;

Mixed success in Ashes build-up

Despite press speculation, Pietersen was not picked for the Tests against Bangladesh&amp;mdash;his early season form being dogged by a foot injury;&quot;[http://www.ecb.co.uk/domestic/england-star-shrugs-off-foot-injury,3706,EN.html Pietersen set to make his debut]&quot;, ecb.co.uk. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvban/content/story/209327.html No room for Pietersen in England squad]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-05-15. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;&amp;mdash;but with his county form improving, he was selected for the Twenty20 match against Australia at Southampton, making 34 from 18 balls and taking three catches as England won by 100 runs.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005/AUS_IN_ENG/SCORECARDS/AUS_ENG_TWENTY-20-I_13JUN2005.html England v Australia 20:20, 13 June 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27; 

In the triangular ODI series against Australia and Bangladesh, Pietersen did not get to bat in the first match at The Oval as England won by 10 wickets, but scored 91 off 65 balls in the match in Bristol against Australia.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005/OD_TOURNEYS/NWS/SCORECARDS/AUS_ENG_NWS_ODI3_19JUN2005.html England v Australia ODI, 19 June 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; In the remainder of the triangular series, Pietersen scored quickly, although without other half-centuries. He finished the seven-match series with a total of 278 runs at an average of 46.33.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Events/ENG/National_Westminster_Bank_Series_2005/England_Batting.html Batting and Fielding for England in National Westminster Bank Series 2005], Cricketarchive. Retrieved on 2007-06-05.; 

Pietersen's performances sparked speculation over whether he would be brought into the Test side for The Ashes later in the summer.A BBC poll of 10 respected cricketers resulted in a minor preference for playing Pietersen and Ian Bell in the Batsman (cricket)#Middle order|middle order, with Graham Thorpe missing out.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/4110676.stm Three into two won't go]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2005-06-20. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;

Later in July, Pietersen played in all three matches of the (ODI) NatWest Challenge against Australia. In the final match he was the top scorer for England with 74 runs, however he was forced off the field in the third over of Australia's reply with a groin injury.;McGlashan, Andrew. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvaus/content/story/213353.html Australia show their finest timing]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-06-12. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;

2005 Ashes triumph
Pietersen warming up in the nets at Lord's in September 2005.

Speculation over when Pietersen would play for the Test team was ended in July with the announcement by the England chairman of selectors, David Graveney, that Pietersen had been selected ahead of Graham Thorpe.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/4676287.stm England drop Thorpe for Pietersen]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2005-07-14. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;He made his debut in the first Ashes Test at Lord's, becoming the 626 player to play for the national side.;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/player/caps.html?country=1;class=1 England Caps], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-06-06.; Pietersen scored 57 and 64 not out as England collapsed to a heavy defeat, becoming only the fourth player to top score in both innings on debut for England, the eighth England player to score a half-century in each innings on his debut, and the third cricketer to do so at Lord's.;Lynch, Steven. &quot;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/columns/content/story/214802.html Pietersen's double debut double]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-08-01. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; In the second Test at Edgbaston he scored 71 in the first innings and 20 in the second, with England narrowly winning by 2 runs.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005/AUS_IN_ENG/SCORECARDS/AUS_ENG_T2_04-08AUG2005.html England v Australia Second Test, 4-7 August 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; In the drawn third Test, Pietersen struggled with 21 and 0, then scored 45 and 23 in the fourth as England went 2-1 up.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005/AUS_IN_ENG/SCORECARDS/AUS_ENG_T3_11-15AUG2005.html England v Australia Third Test, 11-15 August 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005/AUS_IN_ENG/SCORECARDS/AUS_ENG_T4_25-29AUG2005.html England v Australia Fourth Test, 25-28 August 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; Under pressure to post a large score in the final Test at The Oval, Pietersen did not contribute significantly in the first innings with 14.In the second innings, Pietersen was dropped twice before reaching double figures, but went on to score his maiden Test century with 158, drawing the match and securing the series for England.;;Grunill, Paul. &quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/4238344.stm Oval hero Pietersen]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2005-09-12. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; His innings included seven sixes, a record for an English player in an Ashes innings.;[http://www.cricinfo.com/db/STATS/TESTS/BATTING/TRIVIA/BAT_MOST_SIXES_TEST.html Tests - Most Sixes in an Innings], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; Pietersen was named Man of the Match for his efforts,;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005/AUS_IN_ENG/SCORECARDS/AUS_ENG_T5_08-12SEP2005.html England v Australia Fifth Test, 8-12 September 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; and finished the series as top scorer, with 473 runs over the five Tests, an average of 52.55.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005/AUS_IN_ENG/STATS/AUS_IN_ENG_JUN-SEP2005_TEST_AVS.html Australia in England, 2005 Test Series Averages], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; However, he had a less successful series in the field, dropping six catches in the five Tests, a point he made wryly when questioned about the Australians dropping him three times on the final day.;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/quote/content/story/231681.html The best quotes of 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;

Pietersen was given an ECB &quot;central contract&quot; to reflect his place in the national side.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/214969.html Pietersen awarded central contract]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-08-03. Retrieved on 2007-05-27;

Less rewarding winter tour

Pietersen had a less successful time in the three Test matches against Pakistan, which England lost 2&amp;ndash;0. He made little impact in the first and third Tests, his highest score being 34.;[http://www.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005-06/ENG_IN_PAK/SCORECARDS/ENG_PAK_T1_12-16NOV2005.html Pakistan v England First Test, 12-16 November 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-29.;;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005-06/ENG_IN_PAK/SCORECARDS/ENG_PAK_T3_29NOV-03DEC2005.html Pakistan v England Third Test, 29 November-03 December, 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; He fared better in the second, however, making his second Test century in the first innings.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/4457390.stm Pietersen &amp; Bell hit England tons]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2005-11-22. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; He was also performing well in the one-day series with two explosive innings of 56 from 39 balls to help England win the first ODI, and 28 from 27 balls in the second.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005-06/ENG_IN_PAK/SCORECARDS/ENG_PAK_ODI1_10DEC2005.html Pakistan v England First ODI, 10 December, 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-29.;;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005-06/ENG_IN_PAK/SCORECARDS/ENG_PAK_ODI2_12DEC2005.html Pakistan v England Second ODI, 12 December, 2005], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; The quick-scoring innings in the second ODI was to be Pietersen's last on the tour. A rib injury sustained in the first ODI proved too painful throughout the second, and Pietersen returned to England to recover fully for the tour of India.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/pakveng/content/story/229473.html Pietersen forced home by rib injury]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2005-12-13. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; 

In March 2006, Pietersen played in the three Tests against India, which England drew 1&amp;ndash;1. His 87 in the second innings of the first match came during England's acceleration period, helping push the required target over 300.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005-06/ENG_IN_IND/SCORECARDS/ENG_IND_T1_01-05MAR2006_BBB-COMMS.html India v England, First Test, 01-05 March, 2005 Ball-by-ball commentary], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.; England then declared overnight, and India successfully batted out the final day to secure a draw. This half-century was followed by another in the first innings of the second Test. The second innings was not so good, facing just 13 balls before being given out caught behind off a Harbhajan Singh delivery.The unhappy Pietersen was later fined 30 percent of his match fee for shaking his head and showing signs of dissent.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/240601.html Pietersen fined for dissent]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-03-13. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; &quot;Replays demonstrated that the ball that had dismissed him had brushed his forearm, not his glove, before ballooning up into the hands of Rahul Dravid at slip. But umpire Darrell Hair gave him out for 4 as England collapsed on the fourth afternoon.&quot;; Pietersen posted scores of 39 and 7 in the final Test, a match England won comfortably after a dismal 100 all out in India's second visit to the crease.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005-06/ENG_IN_IND/SCORECARDS/ENG_IND_T3_18-22MAR2006.html India v England, Third Test, 18-22 March, 2006], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-30.;

In the one-day series, which England lost 5&amp;ndash;1, he was top scorer for England in four out of the five matches he played, and had the highest average of any player with 58.20.;[http://usa.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005-06/ENG_IN_IND/STATS/ENG_IN_IND_FEB-APR2006_ODI_AVS.html England in India, 2005-06 One-day Series Averages], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-29.; His 71 in the second ODI took him past 1,000 ODI runs, equalling Viv Richards' record of 21 innings to reach this total.;[http://www.cricinfo.com/db/STATS/ODIS/BATTING/FASTEST_ODI_CAREER_RUNS/ODI_FASTEST_TO_1000_RUNS.html ODIs - Fastest to 1000 Career Runs], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;

Sri Lanka and Pakistan in England, 2006

Pietersen bowls off-spin in the Adelaide Oval nets in November 2006.
In May 2006, Pietersen matched his highest Test score of 158 in the first match against Sri Lanka,;McGlashan, Andrew. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/246911.html Mahmood and Pietersen leave Sri Lanka in tatters]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-05-12. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; and followed it with 142 in the second Test.;McGlashan, Andrew. &quot;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/engvsl/content/current/story/248428.html Bowlers build on Pietersen's stunning century]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-05-26. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; This took him passed the milestone of 1,000 Test runs, in his 12th Test match, and he became the first batsman since Graham Gooch in 1990 to score a century in three successive Test innings on English soil.;Kumar, Manish. &quot;[http://www.cricketzone.com/news/news_columns/2007-03-08-98.html Will England rise from the Ashes for the World Cup?]&quot;, cricketzone.com, 2007-03-08. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; This performance moved Pietersen into the top ten of the ICC cricket ratings, as he was named the England (Test Match) Player of the Series.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Seasons/ENG/2006_ENG_Sri_Lanka_in_England_2006.html Sri Lanka in England 2006], Cricketarchive. Retrieved 28 May, 2007.;;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/5026308.stm Pietersen moves into Test top 10]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2006-05-29. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;
On the first day of the third Test against Pakistan, Pietersen reached his fifth Test century with an overnight score of 104. Although Pietersen retired hurt shortly after reaching three figures, due to cramp, he returned to the crease the next morning and went on to top score in England's first innings total of 515 with 135 runs from 169 balls.;McGlashan, Andrew. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/story/255643.html Yousuf leads Pakistan reply after Bell's third ton]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-08-05. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;
 
Pietersen bowled his first delivery in Test match cricket on June 4, against Sri Lanka.;[http://content-aus.cricinfo.com/engvsl/engine/match/225266.html England v Sri Lanka Third Test, 2-5 June 2006], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; His first Test wicket came against Pakistan later in the summer when Kamran Akmal got a thin edge through to Geraint Jones.;McGlashan, Andrew. &quot;[http://content-aus.cricinfo.com/engvpak/content/story/253539.html Pakistan ride on Yousuf special]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-07-15. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;

Later in June, Pietersen scored 17 in the Twenty20 International as England lost by 2 runs to Sri Lanka.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/85/85632.html England v Sri Lanka, Twenty20], Cricketarchive, 2006-06-15. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; The twenty over match against Pakistan was no better, Pietersen being bowled by Mohammad Asif for a golden duck as Pakistan helped themselves to a five-wicket victory.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/86/86003.html Pakistan v England, Twenty20], Cricketarchive, 2006-08-28. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;

England in Australia, 2006&amp;ndash;7

In the much anticipated Ashes series in Australia, Pietersen was widely judged to be England's best player, scoring 490 runs in five matches and averaging over 50. He started well with a defiant 92 in the first Test despite England losing by 277 runs,;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/6185580.stm Australia v England - 1st Test]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2006-11-27. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; and then backed up his good form with a century in the second Test in Adelaide,
sharing a 310-run partnership for the fourth wicket with Paul Collingwood. When he was eventually run out, his first reaction was to &quot;giggle&quot; because it was the third time he had scored exactly 158 runs (at that point, his highest Test score).;Miller, Andrew. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/ausveng/content/story/270774.html Pietersen and Collingwood share the limelight]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-12-02. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; However, even Pietersen seemed disheartened by the end of the series, which England lost 5&amp;ndash;0.;Miller, Andrew. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/275400.html Pietersen the best of a poor bunch]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2007-01-06. Retrieved on 2007-01-12.;

In the Twenty20 match, Pietersen was run out on 11, as England lost the match by 77 runs.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/98/98972.html Australia v England, Twenty20]. Cricketarchive, 2007-01-09. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;For a powerful hitter, Pietersen has not posted a large score in the specialised twenty-over format, averaging 15.50.; In the first One-day International of the 2006&amp;ndash;07 Commonwealth Bank Series, on 12 January at the Melbourne Cricket Ground, Pietersen was injured when a ball bowled by Glenn McGrath hit him on the ribs. Despite continuing his innings in some discomfort, making 82, X-rays revealed a fracture and Pietersen was forced to miss the rest of the series.;Coverdale, Brydon. &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/cbs/content/current/story/276237.html Pietersen out of tour with fractured rib]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2007-01-12. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.;

Career in 2007

Inthe 2007 Cricket World Cup, Pietersen crafted 104 runs off 122 balls against Australia in the Super Eight stage of the tournament. It was the first World Cup century by an Englishman since 1996, and the first ever against Australia.;Rajesh, S and Gopalakrishna, HR. &quot;[http://content-aus.cricinfo.com/wc2007/content/current/story/289672.html How Tait and Hogg turned it around]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2007-04-08. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; He made three half-centuries, scoring 60 runs from 92 balls against New Zealand,;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/wc2007/engine/match/247463.html England v New Zealand, 16 March 2007], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; 56 runs from 72 balls against Kenya,;[http://content-sl.cricinfo.com/wc2007/engine/match/247479.html England v Kenya, 24 March 2007], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; and 58 runs from 80 balls against Sri Lanka.;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/stlucia/engine/match/247489.html England v Sri Lanka, 4 April 2007], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; His efforts in the World Cup helped him achieve the status of ICC number-one ranked batsman in the world for ODIs;;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/6494577.stm Pietersen top of world rankings]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2007-03-26. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; however, England did not reach the semi-finals.In England's final match of the World Cup against the West Indies, Pietersen made 100 from 91 balls, and effected the run-out of retiring captain Brian Lara.;Lillywhite, Jamie. &quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/6576083.stm West Indies v England]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2007-04-21. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; This century took him past 2000 ODI runs, in doing so equalling the record 51 matches set by Zaheer Abbas.; He finished the tournament with 444 runs, at an average of 55.5, and was described as shining in the England team &quot;like a 100 watt bulb in a room full of candles&quot;.;Goughy, Kev. &quot;[http://www.cricketweb.net/article.php?CategoryIDAuto=4&amp;NewsIDAuto=3885 Team of the 2007 World Cup]&quot;, cricketweb.net, 2007-05-15. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.;

Having scored a century in the first Test against the West Indies at Lord's,;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/engvwi/engine/current/match/258459.html England v West Indies First Test, 17-21 May 2007], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-05-27; Pietersen posted his highest score of 226 in the second Test at Headingley, surpassing his previous best of 158 which he had achieved three times.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/6695535.stm Test-best score thrills Pietersen]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2007-05-26. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; With this score, Pietersen moved ahead of Everton Weekes and Viv Richards to be the batsman with the second-highest run-total out of his first 25 Tests (behind Don Bradman).; It is also the highest Test score for England since Graham Gooch scored 333 against India in 1990.;Mitchell, Kevin. &quot;[http://sport.guardian.co.uk/cricket/story/0,,2089157,00.html?gusrc=rss&amp;feed=7 Peerless Pietersen sets up drubbing]&quot;. The Guardian, 27 May, 2007. Retrieved on 28 May, 2007.; This innings subjected the West Indies to an innings and 283 runs defeat, their largest against any team. Pietersen, the Man of the Match, said, &quot;I believe the recipe for success is hard work. I've been criticised for throwing my wicket away, and I tried to make it count here&quot;.; &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/engvwi/engine/current/match/258460.html?innings=3;view=commentary Commentary:England v West Indies at Leeds, May 25-28, 2007]&quot;. Cricinfo, 2007-05-28. Retrieved on 2007-06-06.;

In the third Test at Old Trafford, scoring 68 in the second innings, Pietersen lost his wicket in a bizarre dismissal when West Indian all-rounder Dwayne Bravo delivered a bouncer which knocked Pietersen's helmet off his head and onto his stumps.He is only the fourth batsman in Test cricket to be dismissed &quot;hit wicket&quot; as a result of headgear falling onto the stumps.;Brett, Oliver. &quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/6737017.stm West Indies v England]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2007-06-09. Retrieved on 2007-06-10.; This score took him past the 8500 first-class runs mark, and 2,500 runs in Test cricket.;[http://www.cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/103/103087/103087_bbb.html England v West Indies 3rd Test match], 2007-06-11, Cricketarchive. Retrieved on 2007-06-11.;

In contrast, Pietersen's batting was poor in the following single innings matches; he scored a total of 77 runs in five matches (two Twenty20 and three ODI), recording a second-ball duck in the final ODI.;[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/103/103096.html England v West Indies 3rd ODI], 2007-07-07, Cricketarchive. Retrieved on 2007-07-07.; He subsequently fell to second in the official One-day International batting rankings, behind Ricky Ponting.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/6121940.stm Pietersen relinquishes top place]&quot;, 2007-07-08, BBC Sport. Retrieved on 2007-07-09.; Pietersen himself has commented that his lack of recent form is a result of &quot;fatigue&quot;, and has reiterated his calls for a less &quot;hectic&quot; match schedule.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/6294522.stm Pietersen blames fatigue for form]&quot;, BBC Sport. Retrieved on 2007-07-12.;

Pietersen found some form in the first Test against India, with a magnificent 134 in the second innings to set up a potential England victory. Pietersen described this as his best century, in very testing conditions.;Miller, Andrew &quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/ci/content/current/story/303195.html 'I'd probably rate that as No. 1']&quot;, 2007-07-22, cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-07-23.; After two low scores in the second Test, Pietersen scored his 10th Test Century in the third and final Test at the Oval, helping England to draw the game with 101.;[http://content-www.cricinfo.com/engvind/engine/match/258470.html England v India Third Test, 9-13 August 2007], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-08-15;

Pietersen was also picked for and played in the Twenty20 Championship in South Africa. In England's first game against Zimbabwe on September 13, Pietersen hit 79 runs off 37 balls including four sixes and seven fours in an English total of 188-9. England won the match by 50 runs, however this was to be Pietersens only significant contribution in the competition.

=Sri Lanka 2007&amp;ndash;8=

Pietersen travelled to Sri Lanka with England's ODI squad in September 2007. He scored 50 in England's warm up game against the Sri Lankan Cricket XI,;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/shared/fds/hi/statistics/cricket/scorecards/2007/9/14133/html/scorecard.stm ''Tour Match: Sri Lanka Cricket XI v England''] BBC News retrieved November 22 2007; however followed this with scores of one,;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/shared/fds/hi/statistics/cricket/scorecards/2007/10/14134/html/scorecard.stm ''ODI vs. Sri Lanka, 1st Match''] BBC News retrieved November 22 2007; twelve,;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/shared/fds/hi/statistics/cricket/scorecards/2007/10/14135/html/scorecard.stm ''ODI vs. Sri Lanka, 2nd Match''] BBC News retrieved November 22 2007; and eight.;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/shared/fds/hi/statistics/cricket/scorecards/2007/10/14136/html/scorecard.stm ''ODI vs. Sri Lanka, 3rd Match''] BBC News retrieved November 22 2007; He then found form with 63 not out from 75 deliveries ;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/shared/fds/hi/statistics/cricket/scorecards/2007/10/14137/html/scorecard.stm ''ODI vs. Sri Lanka, 4th Match''] BBC News retrieved November 22 2007; to clinch a historic series win for England, the first in the country since the 1980s. He went on to score 28 in the final match which was a consolationry victory for Sri Lanka.;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/shared/fds/hi/statistics/cricket/scorecards/2007/10/14138/html/scorecard.stm ''ODI vs. Sri Lanka, 5th Match''] BBC News retrieved November 22 2007; In the first test that followed in November, he was the only batsman not to make double figures in a drawn warm up game against the Board President's XI, being caught for four.;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/7106856.stm ''Cook stars in tame England draw''] BBC News retrieved November 22 2007; In the second warm up match against the Sri Lanka Board XI, Pietersen was again out for a low score in the first innings, surviving just three balls and scoring one run. In the second, however, England snatched a &quot;surprise&quot; win, with Pietersen finding form and hitting 59, the highest score of England's innings.;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/7114383.stm ''England snatch surprise tour win''] BBC News retrieved November 27 2007;

During the test series, however, Pietersen suffered a period of fluctuating form. Scoring 31 and 18 in the first test,;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/shared/fds/hi/statistics/cricket/scorecards/2007/12/14141/html/scorecard.stm ''Test Match Series: Sri Lanka v England''] BBC News retrieved December 20 2007; he managed only a single in the first innings of the second. While he regained his touch for the second innings, with a match saving 45 not out,;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/shared/fds/hi/statistics/cricket/scorecards/2007/12/14142/html/scorecard.stm ''Test Match Series: Sri Lanka v England''] BBC News retrieved December 20 2007; he hit one and 30 in the final test,;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/cricket/england/latest_scorecard/default.stm ''Sri Lanka v England 3rd Test''] BBC News retrieved December 22 2007; passing 3,000 test career runs but averaging only 25.2 across the series, failing to score a half century in a series for the first time in his career,;Hughes, Simon [http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/tms/2007/12/england_series_rankings_1.shtml ''England test series ratings''] BBC News retrieved January 2 2008; and having the second lowest average of all the recognised batsmen.;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/cricket/england/averages/default.stm ''Test Series in Sri Lanka, averages''] BBC News retrieved December 22 2007;

Achievements
=Awards=
Pietersen gained several awards for his performances in the 2005 season. He was named both the ICC ODI Player of the Year and Emerging Player of the Year in 2005,;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/4326586.stm Flintoff shares ICC player award]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2005-10-11. Retrieved on 2007-05-27.; and was one of the five Wisden Cricketers of the Year (alongside team mates Simon Jones and Matthew Hoggard) for his role in the successful Ashes series against Australia.;&quot;[http://content-uk.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/243894.html Flintoff named as the leading player of the year]&quot;, Cricinfo, 2006-04-11. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; Along with the rest of the England team, he was decorated in the 2006 New Year Honours list, being awarded the MBE for his role in the successful Ashes series.;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/4625530.stm Ashes heroes get Palace Honours]&quot;, BBC Sport, 2006-02-09. Retrieved on 2007-05-28.; He also played for the ICC World XI in the ICC Super Series 2005 against Australia.;[http://uk.cricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/2005-06/SUPERS/SUPERS_OCT2005_ICC-XI-SQUAD.html ICC World XI Squads], Cricinfo. Retrieved on 2007-06-06.;

=Test match performance=
Test debut: vs Australia, Lord's, July 21, 2005.;
* He is the batsman with second highest run-total from first 25 Tests (behind Don Bradman).;
* Fourth Englishman to top score in both innings of debut Test.;
* He is one of only twenty-two players to have a peak ICC batting rating over 900.;[http://www.lgiccrankings.com/test/batting/all-time-ranking.php LG ICC Best-Ever Test Batting Ratings], ICC Cricket Rankings. Retrieved on 2007-07-23.;

